      'Boca Raton is one of South Florida\'s most established communities, and a lot of the paver driveways and pool decks through East Boca, the Boca Islands and Old Floresta were laid years ago. Time near the coast is hard on them: the color fades under the sun, black mold builds up in the shade, and the sand between the joints washes out so weeds and ants move in. When the base underneath is still sound, you do not need a rebuild — you need the pavers restored.',
      'We start with a deep clean that pulls the mold, weeds and ground-in grime off the surface, then re-sand the joints with polymeric sand that hardens to lock out weeds and ants for years. The last step is the sealer, and you choose the finish: a matte seal that keeps the natural look, or a wet-look enhancer that deepens the color like the pavers are freshly rinsed.',
      'That seal is what earns its keep this close to the salt air. It shields the color against the relentless Boca sun and the afternoon storms, makes the surface easier to rinse clean, and holds off the mold from coming back. On a canal-front or ocean-side lot it is the difference between pavers that look tired in a season and pavers that hold their color for years.',
    ],
    localNote: 'Coastal and canal-front Boca lots sit in constant salt air and humidity, so mold and joint weeds come back fast — a proper reseal on a maintenance cycle is what keeps them at bay.',
    faqs: [
      { q: 'How often should I reseal my pavers in Boca Raton?', a: 'This close to the coast, plan on every two to four years. The salt air, humidity and strong sun wear a sealer faster here than inland, and resealing on that cycle keeps the color from fading and slows the mold from returning.' },
      { q: 'Will cleaning and re-sanding actually stop the weeds and ants in my joints?', a: 'Yes. Once we deep-clean the joints and refill them with polymeric sand, that sand hardens into a firm bond that locks out the weeds and ants that were living in the loose sand. It is the single biggest reason joints stay clean.' },
      { q: 'Should I choose a matte seal or the wet-look for a coastal Boca home?', a: 'Both protect the pavers the same way. Matte keeps the natural, dry look; the wet-look enhancer deepens the color as if the pavers are freshly rinsed, which many coastal homes like on a pool deck. We show you both on your own pavers at the visit.' },
      { q: 'What does paver cleaning and sealing cost?', a: 'It depends on the square footage and the condition of the pavers, which is why the on-site visit and written estimate are free and itemized. Financing through Wisetack is available so the budget does not decide the timeline.' },
    ],
